## PHASE 1 — Scientific & Mathematical Rubric

### 1.1 Type-system criteria

| # | Criterion | Formal Definition | Pass condition |
|---|-----------|------------------|----------------|
| T1 | **Soundness** | $\forall e.\ \Gamma \vdash e : \tau \Rightarrow \neg \text{stuck}(e)$ | No well-typed program reaches an undefined operation at runtime. |
| T2 | **Principal types** | Damas–Milner: every typable expression has a principal scheme $\sigma^* \le \sigma$ for any other valid $\sigma$. | The inferer must produce $\sigma^*$ (most general). |
| T3 | **Completeness w.r.t. HM** | Every HM-typable program is accepted without annotations. | Strict superset of HM acceptance set. |
| T4 | **Decidability / termination** | Algorithm terminates on all inputs. | Occurs-check + monotone substitution. |
| T5 | **Algorithmic complexity** | Worst-case unification cost. | $O(n \cdot \alpha(n))$ via Union-Find with path compression. |
| T6 | **Diagnostic locality** | An error must be attributable to a span within $O(1)$ AST hops of the true cause. | No "ghost" errors, no global "type variable left unsolved" without origin chain. |
| T7 | **Predictable defaulting** | Any defaulted type variable must be reproducible from a documented rule. | E.g. `Float→f64`, otherwise `i64`. |
| T8 | **Generalization correctness** | $\text{gen}(\Gamma,\tau)$ generalizes only variables not free in $\Gamma$. | No accidental capture; let-poly only at module/let bindings. |

### 1.2 Actor-system criteria

| # | Criterion | Metric |
|---|-----------|--------|
| A1 | **Memory isolation** | No shared mutable state across mailboxes; statically verifiable. |
| A2 | **Message-send latency** | Round-trip $T_{rt}$ on 1-to-1 ping-pong, ≤ 2× C `pthread_cond` baseline. |
| A3 | **Throughput** | Sustained msg/s with bounded mailbox; should remain within constant factor of channel bandwidth. |
| A4 | **Mailbox fairness** | FIFO per sender; bounded starvation $S(n) = O(n)$. |
| A5 | **Backpressure model** | Documented and uniform: blocking, dropping, or `Result`. |
| A6 | **Selective receive** | $O(k)$ in mailbox length, where $k$ is matched prefix. |
| A7 | **Supervision** | Linked failure semantics; restart strategies (one-for-one, etc.). |
| A8 | **Memory model** | Defined happens-before for `send → receive`, equivalent to release/acquire. |

### 1.3 Persistence criteria

| # | Criterion | Bound |
|---|-----------|-------|
| P1 | **Atomicity (single op)** | crash-safe append; recovery deterministic. |
| P2 | **Durability** | `fsync` on commit; recovery POR proof. |
| P3 | **Isolation** | At minimum read-committed; ideally snapshot. |
| P4 | **Write amplification** | $W = \frac{\text{bytes flushed}}{\text{bytes logical}}$; target $W \le 2$. |
| P5 | **Index lookup** | $O(\log n)$ for non-PK; $O(1)$ for PK. |
| P6 | **Schema evolution** | Forward+backward compatible at decode. |
| P7 | **Zero-copy read** | $\text{read}(rec) = \text{mmap}(\text{offset}) + 0$ allocations. |
| P8 | **Concurrency** | Multi-reader/single-writer or MVCC. |

### 1.4 Performance & readability

* **Performance ratio:** $r = T_\text{jade}/T_\text{Clang -O3}$. Pass: geometric mean $r \le 1.10$ across a representative basket; no individual $r > 1.50$.
* **Readability:** measured by **token-density** $\rho = \#\text{tokens}/\#\text{lines}$ vs Python on equivalent programs; tolerance $\rho_\text{jade} \le 1.30 \cdot \rho_\text{py}$.
* **Compile throughput:** $C(n) = n/T_\text{compile}$ (LOC/s). Reference target: ≥ 50 KLOC/s for `--opt 0`.
* **Diagnostic quality:** % of intentional faults yielding span-accurate, single-cause messages on a 50-case test fixture.

### 1.5 Pipeline-architecture rubric

S1 phase modularity (each phase pure-fn over IR), S2 IR validation between phases, S3 single source of optimization truth, S4 single codegen target, S5 deterministic outputs (no HashMap-iteration order leaks), S6 no panic in release path.

